Tonight's northern lights are visible in Yellowknife, Canada. Here's a snapshot from the AuroraMAX HD camera. (Tonight is Monday, November 12, 2012.)
The forecast for tonight from the University of Alaska suggests that the aurora may be visible as far south as Lansing, Michigan. From my Pinterest maps board: Source: gi.alaska.edu via Edward Vielmetti on Pinterest &nbsp;
Some evidence of sightings: The Twitter account @Aurora_Alerts is active when the Northern Lights are active, and it gives very short term forecasts of activity.

